<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/719.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The American Minister will be invited to attend the Te Deum Mass on the
                            14th instant in honor of the election of President Oreste, and to attend
                            a reception after the Mass. Being Dean of the Diplomatic Corps, which
                            will attend these functions, his absence therefrom would be injurious to
                            American influence. Attendance at these functions signifies recognition.
                            Asks instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>